The Twilio SMS API allows you to send and receive SMS messages, manage phone numbers, and more. [Source 1, 2]

Here's a general overview of what you can do with the SMS API:

**1. Sending SMS Messages:**

*   You can send SMS messages using the Programmable SMS API. [Source 7, 8]
*   Here's a basic example using Node.js:

    ```javascript
    // Download the helper library [https://www.twilio.com/docs/node/install](https://www.twilio.com/docs/node/install)
    // Find your Account SID and Auth Token at twilio.com/console
    // Set the environment variables TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID and TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN
    const accountSid = process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID;
    const authToken = process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN;
    const client = require('twilio')(accountSid, authToken);

    client.messages
      .create({
         body: 'This is the ship that made the Kessel Run in fourteen parsecs?',
         from: '+15017250604',
         to: '+15558675310'
       })
      .then(message => console.log(message.sid));
    ```

    *Remember to replace the placeholder values with your actual Account SID, Auth Token, Twilio phone number, and recipient phone number.*
*   This code snippet uses the Twilio Node.js library to send an SMS message.  Make sure you have the library installed (`npm install twilio`). Also, ensure you set the environment variables `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` and `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`.

**2. Receiving SMS Messages:**

*   When someone sends an SMS message to your Twilio phone number, Twilio will send a request to a webhook URL that you configure.
*   You can use this webhook to process the incoming message and take appropriate action.

**3. Key Concepts & Features:**

*   **REST API:** The Twilio APIs are organized around REST principles, making them accessible via HTTP requests. [Source 1, 2]
*   **Messaging Services:**  You can use Messaging Services to simplify scaling and get more features. [Source 5, 6]
*   **A2P 10DLC:** If you're sending SMS messages from local numbers to mobile phones in the US, you may need to register for A2P 10DLC. [Source 3, 4]
* Cross-channel support: You can build customer experiences across SMS, WhatsApp, and other channels [Source 5, 6]
